                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57254_124270 /> Does anticipate supplies will be transported by sea in the performance of any awarded PO/Contract(AA) </b></li>
                <br />
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57254_124271 /> Does <b><u>NOT</u></b> anticipate supplies will be transported by sea in the performance of any awarded PO/Contract (AB</b></li>
            </ul>
        </div>


        <div>
            <p class="ml25">
                <b><i><a href="http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ITAR Part 130</a>, Certification Regarding Political Contributions, Fees, and Commissions </i></b><br> Supplier certifies it <b>SELLS</b> defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Celestica that are:  (i) controlled for export under the U.S. International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR) (22 CFR Parts 120-130); <b>AND</b> (ii) <hint text="Sold $500,000 or more in ITAR controlled goods to Celestica">valued in an amount of $500,000 or more;</hint> <b>AND</b> (iii) for delivery (or incorporation into another product for delivery) to, or for the use of, the armed forces of an international organization or a country other than the United States.<br> Please note 22 CFR ? 130.12(b) requires Supplier to respond to this section <b><u>within 20 days</u></b>, unless supplier provides the information directly to the U.S. State Department in accordance with 22 CFR ? 130.12(c).  U.S. law requires Celestica to inform the Department of State if we have not received a response within 25 days of this request.  Additionally, 22 CFR ? 130.14 requires Supplier to maintain the records upon which the information above is based for a minimum of five (5) years from the date of the report.
            </p>
            <ul class="ml75 hr">
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57255_124272 /> Yes(AA) </b></li>
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57255_124273 /> No(AB)</b></li>
                <br />
                <li>
                    <b>
                        <input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57255_124274 />
                        N/A - Work will be performed outside the US by employees not recruited within the US, District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, Northern Mariana Islands, American Samoa, Guam, US Virgin Islands and Wake Island(AC)
                    </b>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>


        <div>
            <p class="ml25">
                <b><i><a href="http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ITAR Part 130</a>, Certification Regarding Political Contributions, Fees, and Commissions Cont'd</i></b><br> Supplier certifies it has paid, offered to pay, or agreed to pay any "fees", "commissions", or "political contributions" as defined in <a href="http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22#22:1.0.1.13.67.0.32.5" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">22 CFR ? 130.5</a> and <a href="http://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?c=ecfr&SID=9f40509b0e3da13737d77a645b79f912&rgn=div5&view=text&node=22:1.0.1.13.67&idno=22#22:1.0.1.13.67.0.32.6" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">22 CFR ? 130.6</a>, in connection with the sale of defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Celestica.<br> <b>NOTE:</b>  22 CFR ? 130.9(d) requires Supplier to inform Celestica as soon as possible if Supplier subsequently learns that it paid, offered to pay, or agreed to pay any fees, commissions, or political contributions in connection with the sale of defense articles, technical data, and/or defense services to Celestica.<br><br> <span style="color:Red;"><b><i>ADDITIONAL REQUIREMENT:</i></b></span>  If "<b>Yes</b>" selected, please complete <document ="Exhibit 1">Exhibit 1</document>, for <b><u>each</u></b> fee, commission and political contribution, using additional sheets as necessary, referencing the Sales Order/Contract Number at issue, and numbering each successive sheet X of X accordingly.
            </p>
            <ul class="ml75 hr">
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57256_Yes /> Yes </b></li>
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57256_No /> No </b></li>
            </ul>
        </div>



        <div>
            <p class="ml25">
                <b><i><a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=deb9e8b54604fca65359b98927e2da5b&mc=true&tpl=/ecfrbrowse/Title22/22cfr122_main_02.tpl" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">ITAR Part 122</a>, Registration of Manufacturers and Exporters</i></b><br> Under <a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=06bc5afb8078cdaf5983f7e129c77dc3&mc=true&node=se22.1.122_11&rgn=div8" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">22 CFR ? 122.1(a) </a> of the International Traffic in Arms Regulations (ITAR), all companies that engage in the business of manufacturing or exporting defense articles or furnishing defense services are required to register annually with the US Department of State, Directorate of Defense Trade Controls (DDTC).<br> The DDTC administers the ITAR and controls the export and re-export of defense articles and the provision of defense services involving all products listed on the US Munitions List <a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=6555af482ca2be3f998c04b6efd1ca79&mc=true&node=se22.1.121_11&rgn=div8" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">22 CFR ? 121.1</a>: Is your company registered with the DDTC to manufacture defense articles?<br> <span style="color:Red;"><b><i>PLEASE NOTE:</i></b></span>  If response is"<b><i>No</i></b>" and your company is selected to manufacture ITAR controlled items by Celestica Intl Inc, you will be required to register per <a href="https://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID=06bc5afb8078cdaf5983f7e129c77dc3&mc=true&node=se22.1.122_11&rgn=div8" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">22 CFR ? 122.1(a)</a>.
            </p>
            <ul class="ml75 hr">
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57257_124275 /> Yes(AB) </b></li>
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57257_124276 /> No(AA) </b></li>
                <br />
                <li><b><input type="checkbox" @ViewBag.Checkbox57257_124277 /> N/A - Our company does not manufacture defense articles (i.e., ITAR-controlled items)(AC)) </b></li>
            </ul>
        </div>


        <div>
            <p class="ml25">
                <b><i><a href="http://www.gpo.gov/fdsys/search/pagedetails.action?browsePath=Title+14%2FChapter+I%2FSubchapter+H%2FPart+145&granuleId=CFR-2011-title14-vol3-part145&packageId=CFR-2011-title14-vol3&collapse=true&fromBrowse=true&bread=true" rel="nofollow me noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">14 CFR 145, Subpart B</a>, Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) Anti-Drug and Alcohol Misuse Prevention Programs:</i></b><br> Is your company a FAA Approved Repair Station?  ()
            </p>
